node.text: It looks like Nurse Mike Linares is back at it again! For any of you nursing students out there, @SimpleNursing.com_ is a life-saving resource you didn’t know you couldn’t live without! They help thousands of students each year pass their nursing exams and the NCLEX. Do yourself a favor and follow for free content! P.S. I used this myself during my undergrad and can I say I’m totally #fangirling ?! #sponsored #fangirl

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by NURSESOFINSTAGRAM™ on July 23, 2021 tagging @nurselifern. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
Ebi,
Our light in the darkness. You have changed the nursing community forever. You have been the voice we’ve never had, the path of communication from nurses all over the world, the ears to listen to the sadness, frustration, and wins through it all, especially COVID. The world will never be the same without you, but you have left an imprint on the hearts of nurses everywhere. We will forever remember your legacy.  Please find the link in bio to donate, or join @bethematch to honor Ebi.❤️ 🕊

node.text:
Closed! Congratulations!
First place winner is: @samfrytie
Second place winner is: @susanroll199 🚨 GIVEAWAY ALERT! 🚨

As a big thank you to all the nurses of Instagram (& because I love the kiddos 👶), two speech-language pathologists from New York would like to give away a copy of their children’s book about the pandemic. This story is a wonderful keepsake that reminds kids of all the important ways our communities stepped up (including healthcare workers!) during times of crisis. It thanks children for their creativity and resilience, and includes scrapbook pages for families to document their journeys. 

Since the book was published, this SLP duo has continued to spread love through words and art. Enter below to win some of their best products, including printable coloring cards just in time for Father’s Day! Swipe through to see details. 

Here’s how to enter:
1. Follow @nursesofinstagram and @speechandgo
2. Tag friends in the comments - the more friends you tag, the more entries!
3. Share to your story and tag us for an extra entry
